==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Genette
<hw>Ge*nette"</hw>
<pr>(j⟦esl⟧*n⟦ecr⟧t")</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>genette</ets>, Sp. <ets>gineta</ets>, fr. Ar.
<ets>jarnei⟦tsdot⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of several species of small Carnivora of the genus <gen>Genetta</gen>,
allied to the civets, but having the scent glands less developed, and
without a pouch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The common genet (<spn>Genetta vulgaris</spn>) of
Southern Europe, Asia Minor, and North Africa, is dark gray, spotted
with black. The long tail is banded with black and white. The Cape genet
(<spn>Genetta felina</spn>), and the berbe (<spn>Genetta pardina</spn>),
are related African species.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fur of the common genet (<spn>Genetta
vulgaris</spn>); also, any skin dressed in imitation of this
fur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Genet</ent>⟦br⟧
